> @JaroslavTulach Could we set the proxy configuration as an optional? 

If I read correctly your changes, then running with `ant -Dproxy.host+port=manual` would disable the `configureproxy` task in `default.xml`, right?

> a lot of requests to the apache infra when the build script tries to configure it in every submodule.

The other idea would be to compute `configureproxy` only once per build. Maybe enhance `ConfigureProxy` task with a property:
```java
public void skipWhenConfigured(boolean skip) {
}
```
which would check values of 
```
                sysprops.get(ProxySetup.HTTP_PROXY_HOST);
                sysprops.get(ProxySetup.HTTP_PROXY_PORT);
                sysprops.get(ProxySetup.HTTPS_PROXY_HOST);
                sysprops.get(ProxySetup.HTTPS_PROXY_PORT);
```
and if one of them is set do nothing? The Ant XML would then be more simple and the proxy configuration would be done just once per JVM. 

One more idea is to call `SetProxy` task directly from `ConfigureProxy` - at the end that's what we do: use `configureproxy` to set some properties and then call `setproxy`.

The final idea: Once we get `configureproxy` working fine - maybe we should donate the changes to Ant's `SetProxy` task - I have a feeling many Ant users would welcome that...

As per comment on dev@ if you're looking to shorten the method names (which isn't a bad idea) then I'd propose -

```
Optional<T> find(Class<T> clazz);
Stream<T> findAll(Class<T> clazz);
```

Yes, I'd also like to see a Stream returning method if we have this, and I think `find()` or a similar word mirrors `lookup()` better than `maybe()` does.

